Hello Jigar,

It seems that all that is left to be crawled are sites that are 
problematic. -2 means that we failed to connect to a server.

Every time you have an error fetching an URI, it would be deferred for a 
retry. Default delay between retries is 15 minutes and maximum number of 
retires is 30. So, if you have problems fetching an URI, you will spend 
at least 7.5 hours of waiting and retiring if the problem persists.

Consult the frontier report (reports tab in WUI) to see what is left to 
be crawled.

To learn more about Heritrix crawl.log status codes please see FAQs or 
the user manual.

I hope this helps.
